'''赤堀氨基酸反应'''（Akabori amino acid reaction）有两种：
#α-[[氨基酸|氨基酸]]在加热时被[[氧化性|氧化性]][[糖|糖]][[氧化|氧化]]。
[[File:Akabori.png|center]]
#α-[[氨基酸|氨基酸]]及其[[酯|酯]]类被[[钠汞齐|钠汞齐]]在[[氯化氢|氯化氢]]的[[乙醇|乙醇]]溶液中还原，生成 α-[[氨基|氨基]][[醛|醛]]。
[[File:Akabori2.png|center]]

There are several '''Akabori amino acid reactions''', which are named after [[Shirō_Akabori|Shirō Akabori]] ([[Japanese_language|jap.]] 赤堀 四郎) (1900–1992), a Japanese chemist.

In the first reaction, an α-[[amino_acid|amino acid]] is [[oxidised|oxidised]] and undergoes [[decarboxylation|decarboxylation]] to give an [[aldehyde|aldehyde]] at the former [[Alpha_and_beta_carbon|α position]] by heating with [[oxygen|oxygen]] in the presence of a [[reducing_sugar|reducing sugar]].<ref>{{cite journal|author=S. Akabori|title=Studies on amino acids and its derivatives. I. Oxidation of sugars for α-amino acids|journal=J. Chetn. Soc. Japan, Pure Chem. Sect|volume= 52|pages= 606–810|year=1931}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|author=S. Akabori|journal=[[Chem._Ber.|Chem. Ber.]]|volume= 66|page= 143|year=1933|doi=10.1002/cber.19330660213|title=Oxydativer Abbau von α-Amino-säuren durch Zucker|language=de|issue=2}}</ref> This reaction is useful for preparing dichlorophthalimido derivatives{{how|date=June 2017}} of peptides for mass spectral analysis.<ref>{{cite journal|title=Akabori Amino Acid Reaction|journal=Comprehensive Organic Name Reactions and Reagents|volume=8|pages= 29–32|year=2010|doi=10.1002/9780470638859.conrr008}}</ref>

[[File:Reacción_de_Akabori_1.png|File:Reacción de Akabori 1.png]]

In the second reaction, an α-[[amino_acid|amino acid]], or an [[ester|ester]] of it, is reduced by [[sodium_amalgam|sodium amalgam]] and ethanolic HCl to give an α-amino [[aldehyde|aldehyde]].<ref>{{cite journal|author=A. Lawson, H.V. Motley|journal=[[J._Chem._Soc.|J. Chem. Soc.]]|year= 1955|pages= 1695|doi=10.1039/jr9550001695|title=2-Mercaptoglyoxalines. Part IX. The preparation of 1 : 5-disubstituted 2-mercaptoglyoxalines from α-amino-acids}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|author=A. Lawson|journal=[[J._Chem._Soc.|J. Chem. Soc.]] |year=1956|pages= 307|doi=10.1039/jr9560000307|title=63. The reaction of cyanamide with α-amino-acetals and α-amino-aldehydes}}</ref> This process is conceptually similar to the [[Bouveault–Blanc_reduction|Bouveault–Blanc reduction]]<ref>{{cite journal|last1 = Bouveault|first1 = Louis|authorlink1 = Louis Bouveault|last2 = Blanc|first2 = Gustave Louis|journal = [[Compt._Rend.|Compt. Rend.]]|year = 1903|volume = 136|pages = 1676–1678|title = Préparation des alcools primaires au moyen des acides correspondants|language = fr|trans-title = Preparation of primary alcohols by means of the corresponding acids|url = http://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/bpt6k3091c/f1676.image.langFR|access-date = 2019-03-08|archive-date = 2019-03-27|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20190327091534/https://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/bpt6k3091c/f1676.image.langFR|dead-url = no}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1 = Bouveault|first1 = Louis|authorlink1=Louis Bouveault|last2 = Blanc|first2 = Gustave Louis|journal = [[Compt._Rend.|Compt. Rend.]]|year = 1903|volume = 137|pages = 60–62|title = Préparation des alcools primaires au moyen des acides correspondants|language = fr|trans-title = Preparation of primary alcohols by means of the corresponding acids}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|last1 = Bouveault|first1 = Louis|authorlink1 = Louis Bouveault|last2 = Blanc|first2 = Gustave Louis|journal = [[Bull._Soc._Chim._Fr.|Bull. Soc. Chim. Fr.]]|year = 1904|volume = 31|pages = 666–672|title = Transformation des acides monobasiques saturés dans les alcools primaires correspondants|language = fr|trans-title = Transforming saturated monobasic acids into the corresponding primary alcohols|url = http://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/bpt6k5469971k/f670.image|access-date = 2019-03-08|archive-date = 2019-11-15|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20191115083854/https://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/bpt6k5469971k/f670.image|dead-url = no}}</ref> except that it stops at the aldehyde stage rather than reducing the ester all the way to two [[alcohol|alcohol]]s.

